    • Appointment

      public Appointment​(java.lang.String title, java.lang.String description, java.lang.String location, java.lang.String type, java.time.ZonedDateTime start, java.time.ZonedDateTime end, java.time.ZonedDateTime createDate, java.lang.String createdBy, java.time.ZonedDateTime lastUpdate, java.lang.String lastUpdatedBy, int customerID, int userID, int contactID)
      Allows the creation of an Appointment without an ID. IDs are auto-generated by database. To initially add an Appointment, one must be created without an ID.
      Parameters:
      title - Appointment title.
      description - Appointment description.
      location - Appointment location.
      type - Appointment type.
      start - UTC Zoned start date and time for Appointment.
      end - UTC Zoned end date and time for Appointment.
      createDate - UTC Zoned creation date and time for Appointment.
      createdBy - User that created the Appointment.
      lastUpdate - UTC Zoned date and time for last Appointment update.
      lastUpdatedBy - User that last updated the Appointment.
      customerID - ID of the Customer for whom the Appointment is for.
      userID - ID of the User who created the Appointment.
      contactID - ID of the company employee/contact assigned the Appointment.
